Color is one of the most powerful tools in web design. It creates visual hierarchy, conveys meaning, and establishes brand identity. CSS provides multiple ways to specify colors.<br><br><strong>CSS named colors:</strong> CSS includes 147 named colors like <kbd>steelblue</kbd>, <kbd>coral</kbd>, <kbd>gold</kbd>, and <kbd>tomato</kbd>. These are easy to remember and read.<br><br><strong>The background-color property:</strong> Sets the fill color behind an element's content and padding areas.<br><br><pre>.card {
  background-color: lightblue;
}</pre>
